  "summary": "After Adela Marchmont leaves with a five-hundred-pound check, David Hunter confronts Rosaline Claude about her decision to give the money away. David argues that Rosaline is wealthy because Gordon Claude died without a will, and he warns her against providing further financial assistance to the Claude family, noting that her sense of guilt is an inconvenience to him.\n\nDavid then questions Rosaline about Lynne Marchmont’s whereabouts and learns that Lynne has gone to Longleigh to visit Rolly. Irritated by Lynne's relationship with Rolly, David intercepts her on a staircase halfway up a hill. He mocks Rolly and questions Lynne's upcoming June wedding, but Lynne passionately asserts her love for Rolly. During their tense encounter, David notices a woman, whom Lynne identifies as Francis, crossing a door above Frobenk. David informs Lynne that her mother, Adela, has already received five hundred pounds and reveals that other family members, including Aunt Kitty and the doctor, are also seeking funds. Distressed by this news, Lynne runs back toward the farm.\n\nDavid later enters the house through the French doors and finds Francis Claude speaking to Rosaline. Francis explains that Gordon's death has left Jeremy Claude in a desperate financial situation. She cites various reasons, including mortgage loans and government regulations, to justify a request for one million pounds. David remains skeptical of Francis's claims regarding Jeremy's economic plight, recognizing her talent for storytelling.",
